HEADWORD: Breech sight
<hw>Breech" sight`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <def>A device attached to the
breech of a firearm, to guide the eye, in conjunction with the front
sight, in taking aim.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

